owl:Ontology.terms:description: Devices, actuations and measurement-related information for the EEPSA Ontology.
owl:Ontology.terms:title: Measurements for EEPSA (Energy Efficiency Prediction Semantic Assistant) Ontology
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: Information about changes compared to version 0.2 ********************************************************* • The SSN ontology is now imported.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The observations made by the sensors are affected by the direction of the sensing device. This property allows observations of the sensor to be associated to the Direction concept.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has Direction

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A reference to the unit of measure of a quantity (variable or constant) of interest.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: unit

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links an object with an Actuation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has actuation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Determines the period to which it is exposed to sun.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has sun exposure period

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The temperature sought within a space.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: temperature setpoint

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Represents the number of AHU (Air-Handling Unit) that are scheduled to be activated.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: number of active AHUs

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The date when an Actuation is scheduled to happen.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: schedule date

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The date time when an Actuation is scheduled to happen.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: schedule date time

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The time when an Actuation is scheduled to happen.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: schedule time

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Metric unit of atmospheric pressure equal to 14.50 pounds per square inch (lb/in2), 1.02 kilograms per square centimeter (kg/cm2), 29.53 inches of mercury (in Hg), or 0.9869 atmosphere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Bar

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A plane angle unit which is equal to 1/360 of a full rotation or pi/180 rad.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Degree Angle

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Electric current is the flow of electric charge. It is a base quantity in the International System of Units. Electric current is electric charge divided by time. Electric Current is the flow (movement) of electric charge. The amount of electric current through some surface, e.g., a section through a copper conductor, is defined as the amount of electric charge flowing through that surface over time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electric Current

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The rate of change of the velocity of a particle with respect to time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Acceleration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The acceleration at a given instant of time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Instantaneous Acceleration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Accelerometers are used to automatically determine the orientation in which the user is holding the IoT Object (portrait or landscape).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Accelerometer

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Usually measured using Air Quality Index (AQI), it is the measure of Air Pollution in the environment. It is similar to Air Quality.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Air Pollution Quantity Kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Usually measured using an air quality index (AQI) that is a number used by government agencies to communicate to the public how polluted the air currently is or how polluted it is forecast to become. Different countries have their own air quality indices, corresponding to different national air quality standards. It is the measure of Air Quality of the environment. It is similar to Air Pollution. (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Air Quality Quantity Kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device to measure the Air temperature of either indoor or outdoor atmosphere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Air Thermometer

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a unit of electric current, or amount of electric charge per second.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Microampere (uA)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the rate of change of angular displacement and is a vector quantity (more precisely, a pseudovector) that specifies the angular speed (rotational speed) of an object and the axis about which the object is rotating. (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Angular Speed

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The pressure exerted by the atmosphere as a consequence of gravitational attraction exerted upon the column of air lying directly above the point in question.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Atmospheric Pressure

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Atmospheric Pressure Sensor, Barometer or Barometric Pressure Sensor is a scientific instrument used in meteorology to measure atmospheric pressure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Atmospheric Pressure Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of the percentage of the battery capacity that remains available.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Battery Level Quantity Kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of board temperature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Board Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to measure board temperature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Board Thermometer

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of building or room temperature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Building/Room Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Carbon Dioxide (CO2) measure in the atmosphere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Carbon Dioxide (CO2) Quantity Kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Carbon Dioxide (CO2) Sensor used to measure level of CO2 in the atmosphere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Carbon Dioxide (CO2) Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device to detect Carbon Monoxide (CO) in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Carbon Monoxide (CO) Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Candela is the luminous intensity, in a given direction, of a source that emits monochromatic radiation of frequency 540 x 10^12 hertz and that has a radiant intensity in that direction of 1/683 watt per steradian. (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Candela

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of the ability of a system to store an electric charge.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Capacitance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The centibar is a unit of pressure defined as 1e-2 bar.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Centibar

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A metric unit of length, equal to one hundredth of a metre.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Centimetre, Centimeter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of Chemical Agent Atmospheric Concentration
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Chemical Agent Atmospheric Concentration Quantity Kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of the concentration of chemical particles suspended in the atmosphere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Air Particles Chemical Agent Atmospheric Concentration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of the concentration of Carbon Monoxide (CO) gas suspended in the atmosphere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Carbon Monoxide (CO) Chemical Agent Atmospheric Concentration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of the concentration of NO2 gas suspended in the atmosphere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: NO2 Chemical Agent Atmospheric Concentration

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of cloud cover at a certain time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cloud Cover Quantity Kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Cloud Cover Sensor is used to detect whether it is sunny, cloudy, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cloud Cover Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of ability to conduct electricity. It is measured in siemens per meter (S/m).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Conductivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to measure the conductivity of a system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Conductivity Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Triples for location in the (Latitude, Longitude, Altitude) format.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Coordinates

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: SI unit of electric charge.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Coulomb

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Day is a unit of time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Day

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Decibel is a logarithmic unit used to express the ratio of two values of a physical quantity. It is often used to measure sound level.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Decibel (dB)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sound pressure sensed by the human ear.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DecibelA (dB(A))

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Degree

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Degree Celsius

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measurement Unit to represent temperature on the Fahrenheit scale.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Degree Fahrenheit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Difference between Dewpoint and surface temperatures.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Delta Dew Point

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device that measures the difference between Dewpoint and surface temperatures.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Delta Dew Point Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the temperature to which air must be cooled at constant pressure to condense to form liquid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dew Point

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device that measures dew point.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dew Point Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The temperature at which dew forms and is a measure of atmospheric moisture. It is the temperature to which air must be cooled at constant pressure and water content to reach saturation. A higher dew point indicates more moisture in the air; a dew point greater than 20 Degree C (68 Degree F) is considered uncomfortable and greater than 22 Degree C (72 Degree F) is considered to be extremely humid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dew Point Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Without dimensions; having no appreciable or noteworthy extent. Without physical meaning.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dimensionless

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The geodetic azimuth of the direction towards which an object is point to.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Direction Azimuth

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of how far apart objects are.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Distance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Distance Sensor is used to detect distance between two objects for example: the safety distance with other cars. Distance sensor can be a laser.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Distance Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Unit to measure Air Quality in European cities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: European Air Quality Index (EAQI)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the physical property of matter that causes it to experience a force when placed in an electromagnetic field. (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electric Charge

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Electric field is the electric force per unit charge.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electric Field

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A field of force associated with a moving electric charge equivalent to an electric field and a magnetic field at right angles to each other and to the direction of propagation. Applied to the 1800 MHz UHF band.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electric Field 1800 MHz

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A field of force associated with a moving electric charge equivalent to an electric field and a magnetic field at right angles to each other and to the direction of propagation. Applied to the 2100 MHz UHF band.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electric Field 2100 MHz

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A field of force associated with a moving electric charge equivalent to an electric field and a magnetic field at right angles to each other and to the direction of propagation. Applied to the 2400 MHz UHF band.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electric Field 2400 MHz

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A field of force associated with a moving electric charge equivalent to an electric field and a magnetic field at right angles to each other and to the direction of propagation. Applied to the 900 MHz UHF band.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electric Field 900 MHz

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Electric potential is the potential energy per unit charge associated with static (time-invariant) electric field.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electric Potential

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The electrical resitance of an electrical conductor is the opposition to the passage of an electric current through that conductor.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electrical Resistance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Electrical Sensor.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electrical Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Energy is the property that must be transferred to an object in order to perform work on. (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Energy

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sensor to measure power or energy consumption.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Energy Meter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Property used to determine the level a certain object such as waste bin is filled upto.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Fill Level

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Frequency is the number of occurrences of a repeating event per unit time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Frequency

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect the frequency.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Frequency Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The amount of fuel a vehicle uses to travel a particular distance at a particular speed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Fuel Consumption Quantity Kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A measure that displays the instantaneous fuel consumption of a vehicle during its operation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Fuel Consumption Instantaneous

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Accumulated amount of fuel used during vehicle operation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Fuel Consumption Total

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect fuel level in a system such a car.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Fuel Level Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device that allows an object to localize itself.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GPS Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device that detects the presence of gases in an area, often as part of a safety system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gas Detector

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect poisonous gaseous in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gaseous Pollutant Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Gauss is the CGS unit of measurement of magnetic flux density (or magnetic induction) (B) (Source Wikipedia)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gauss

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a metric system unit of mass
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gram (g)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is defined by mass in grams divided by volume in cubic metres.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gram Per Cubic Metre

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It shows how many grams of a certain substance are present in one liter of a usually liquid or gaseous mixture.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gram Per Liter (g/L)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A gyrometer is an instrument which measures an angular speed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gyrometer Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A gyroscope is a device for measuring or maintening orientation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gyroscope Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to measure of hydrogen sulfide in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: H2S Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The SI unit of frequency, equal to one cycle per second.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Hertz

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Hour of the day.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Hour

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of Household Appliance Temperature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Household Appliance Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Humidity sensor or hygrometer is an instrument used for measuring the moisture concent in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Humidity Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Illuminance is the total luminous flux incident on a surface, per unit area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Illuminance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sensor that detects and conveys the information that constitutes an image.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Length in inches.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Inch

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Arbitrary indirect reference which should be translated into meaningful measurements by using the corresponding decoding algorithm detailed in the resource description. In this case the returned values can only take certain values from a finite set.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Index

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Kelvin is a unit of measurement for temperature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Kelvin, Degree Kelvin

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of electrical energy equivalent to a power consumption of one thousand watts for one hour.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Kilo Watt Hour

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a unit of data transfer rate equal to: 1,000 bits per second.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Kilobits Per Second

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The SI unit of mass, it is equal to the mass of the international prototype of the kilogram.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Kilogram (kg)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is SI derived unit of density, defined by mass in kilograms divided by volume in cubic metres.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Kilogram Per Cubic Metre, Kilogram Per Cubic Meter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a unit of speed, expressing the number of kilometres travelled in one hour.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Kilometer Per Hour

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A metric unit of measurement equal to 1,000 metres (approx 0.62 miles).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Kilometre, Kilometer

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Leaf wetness is a meteorological parameter that describes the amount of dew and precipitation left on surfaces. It is used for monitoring leaf moisture for agricultural purposes, such as fungus and disease control, for control of irrigation systems, and for detection of fog and dew conditions, and early detection of rainfall. (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Leaf Wetness

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Leaf Wetness Sensor is used in agriculture to check whether the plants need to be watered.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Leaf Wetness Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Light/Illuminance Sensor is used to adjust the brightness of the surface.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Light Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A metric unit of capacity defined as the volume of one kilogram of water under standard conditions. It is equal to 1,000 cubic centimetres.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Liter, Litre

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A consumption unit which is equal to the one of a vehicle which needs 1 fuel litre in order to traverse 100 kilometres.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Litre Per 100 Kilometres, Liter Per 100 Kilometers

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A particular place or position.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Location Quantity Kind

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The SI unit of luminous flux, equal to the amount of light emitted per second in a unit solid angle of one steradian from a uniform source of one candela.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Lumen (lm)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Luminous Flux is the measure of the perceived power of light.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Luminous Flux

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a measure of the wavelength-weighted power emitted by a light source in a particular direction per unit solid angle, based on the luminosity function, a standardized model of the sensitivity of the human eye. The SI unit of luminous intensity is the candela (cd), an SI base unit. (Source Wikipedia)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Luminous Intensity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The SI unit of illuminance, equal to one lumen per square metre.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Lux (lx)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A region around a magnetic material or a moving electric charge within which the force of magnetism acts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Magnetic Field

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the magnetic flux through a surface is the surface integral of the normal component of the magnetic field (B) passing through that surface. The SI unit of magnetic flux is the weber (Wb). (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Magnetic Flux Density

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A magnetometer is an device that measures magnetism—either magnetization of magnetic material like a ferromagnet, or the strength and, in some cases, direction of the magnetic field at a point in space. (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Magnetometer

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Mass is a property of a physical body. It is the measure of an object's resistance to acceleration when a net force is applied.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mass

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the unit of length.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Meter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A speed/velocity unit which is equal to the speed of an object traveling 1 meter distance in one second.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Meter Per Second (m/s)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the unit of acceleration.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Meter Per Second Square

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect Methane in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Methane (CH4) Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a unit of electric current, or amount of electric charge per second.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Microampere (uA)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a unit of mass equal to one billionth (1×10^−9) of a kilogram.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Microgram (ug)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Microgram per cubic metre is a unit of density defined as microgram divided by cubic metre. Milligram per cubic metre is a derived unit in the International System of Units.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Microgram Per Cubic Metre, Microgram Per Cubic Meter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a unit of electromotive force or potential difference equal to one millionth of a volt.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Microvolt (uV)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a unit of power.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Microwatt (uW)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of the number of miles or the average distance that a vehicle can travel on a specified quantity of fuel
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mileage

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The distance which can be travelled by the vehicle before the next service inspection is required. A negative distance is transmitted if the service inspection has been passed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mileage Distance To Service

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mileage Total

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a unit of length that is equal to 1,760 yards (approx. 1.609 kilometres).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Miles

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: One thousandth of an ampere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Milliampere (mA)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: One thousandth of a bar.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Millibar

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: One thousandth of a gram.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Milligram (mg)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a density measurement unit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Milligram Per Cubic Metre, Milligram Per Cubic Meter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A dose unit which is equal to 1 milligram of a substance per square meter of surface area of the recipient subject.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Milligram Per Square Metre

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: One thousandth of a litre (0.002 pint).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Millilitre

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A unit of both speed (scalar) and velocity (vector), defined as the distance of one millimeter travelled per unit hour.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Millimeter Per Hour, Millimetre Per Hour

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: One thousandth of a metre (0.039 in).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Millimetre, Millimeter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: One thousandth of a second.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Millisecond

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: One thousandth of a volt.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Millivolt (mV)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a measure of the intensity of the signal of a radio transmitter.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Millivolt Per Meter, Millivolt Per Metre

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A unit of power equal to one thousandth of a watt.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Milliwatt (mW)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A Minute of Angle (MOA) is an angular measurement. A MOA is 1/60th of a degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Minute Angle

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A unit of time equal to 60 seconds or 1/60th of an hour.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Minute Time

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A millimeter of mercury is a manometric unit of pressure, formerly defined as the extra pressure generated by a column of mercury one millimetre high and now defined as precisely 133.322387415 pascals. It is denoted by the symbol mmHg. It is used to measure blood pressure measurements (systolic and diastolic).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MmHg

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the amount of a substance that corresponds to its formula mass in milligrams. MmolPerLiter is used to measure cholesterol.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mmol Per Liter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the action or process of moving or being moved.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Motion

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicator of whether a person (or object) is detected upon his/her/its movement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Motion State

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect NH3 level in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: NH3 Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sensor detecting levels of Nitrogen Dioxide (NO2) in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Nitrogen Dioxide (NO2) Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect Nitrogen Oxide (NO) in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Nitrogen Oxide (NO) Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect Ozone (O3) in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ozone (O3) Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect if on object is occupied or not.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Occupancy Detector

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ohm is the unit of electrical resistance.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ohm

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Okta is the unit to measure the cloud cover.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Okta

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect Oxygen (O2) in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Oxygen Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a numeric scale used to specify the acidity or basicity of an aqueous solution.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PH

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect PH level.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PH Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It describes the concentration of something in water or soil.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PPM (parts per million)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Unit for pressure (e.g., atmospheric pressure).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pascal

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A unit of weight equal to 16 oz. 1 pound= 453.592 grams
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pound

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the rate, per unit time, at which electrical energy is transferred by an electric circuit.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Power

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is any product of the condensation of atmospheric water vapor that falls under gravity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Precipitation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a device measuring the amount of precipitation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Precipitation Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure to know if an object is present. It is usually boolean.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Presence

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The presence or absence of people passing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Presence State People

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the physical force exerted on or against an object by something in contact with it.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pressure

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A device used to detect pressure. For example, it can be attached on the bed to infer if the user is lying, sleeping, sitting, bed occupancy, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pressure Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure to detect proximity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Proximity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Detect if something is within proximity of a sensor.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Proximity Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The radian is a unit of angular measure defined such that an angle of one radian subtended from the center of a unit circle produces an arc with arc length 1.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Radian

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The radian per second is defined as the change in the orientation of an object, in radians, every second. The radian per second is the SI unit of angular (rotational) speed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Radian Per Second

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The depth of precipitation (water-equivalent) that accumulated over a measurement time quantity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Rainfall

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The portion of electricity that establishes and sustains the electric and magnetic fields of alternating-current equipment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Reactive Power

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The ratio of vapour pressure to saturation vapour pressure, where vapour pressure is the pressure exerted by the molecules of water vapour and saturation vapour pressure is the pressure exerted by molecules of water vapour in AIR that has attained saturation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Relative Humidity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Revolutions per minute (abbreviated rpm, RPM, rev/min, r/min) is a measure of the frequency of rotation, specifically the number of rotations around a fixed axis in one minute. It is used as a measure of rotational speed of a mechanical component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Revolutions Per Minute

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ratio of time on which a road lane section is occupied by vehicles within a given period of time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Road Occupancy

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to measure the road Surface temperature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Road Surface Thermometer

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Temperature of the road.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Road Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Temperature of a room.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Room Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device use to detect Sulphur Dioxide (SO2) level in the environment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sulphur Dioxide (SO2) Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the measure of all the salts dissolved in water.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Salinity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device use to detect salinity of water.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Salt Meter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Arbitrary indirect reference which should be translated into meaningful measurements by using the corresponding decoding algorithm detailed in the resource description. In this case the returned values are part of a continuous variable which can take any numeric value.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Scale

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a unit of angular measurement equal to 1/60 of one degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Second Angle

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Qualitatively defined as the second division of the hour by sixty, the first division by sixty being the minute. SI definition of second is "the duration of 9 192 631 770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the cesium 133 atom.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Second Time

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Shake sensor is used to deduce the quality of the road, earthquakes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Shake Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect if there is a fire or the smoke.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Smoke Detector

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the quantity of water contained in a material, such as soil.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Soil Humidity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the quantity of water contained in a material, such as soil.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Soil Humidity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The force per unit area required to remove film water from soil.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Soil Moisture Tension

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Soil temperature is the bulk temperature of the soil, not the surface (skin) temperature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Soil Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the power per unit area received from the Sun in the form of electromagnetic radiation in the wavelength range of the measuring instrument. (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Solar Radiation Measurement, PAR Measurement (Photosynthetically Active Radiation)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect Solar Radiation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Solar Radiation Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The rate at which someone or something moves or operates or is able to move or operate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Speed

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The rate at which someone or something moves or operates or is able to move or operate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Speed

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A measure of the instantaneous rate of motion of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Speed Instantaneous

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A measure of the median rate of motion of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Speed Median

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sensor used to detect speed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Car Speed Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The position of the Sun in the sky is a function of both time and the geographic coordinates of the observer on the surface of the Earth. (Source Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sun Position Direction

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sensor used to detect sun position.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sun Position Direction Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the altitude of the sun, the angle between the horizon and the centre of the sun's disc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sun Position Elevation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect sun elevation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sun Position Elevation Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the air temperature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the SI unit of magnetic flux density.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Tesla

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A device to measure the temperature in a room or outside.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Thermometer

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sequence of characters or encoded information identifying when a certain event occurred, usually giving date and time of day, sometimes accurate to a small fraction of a second. This representation should be encoded following ISO8601.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Timestamp

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is a non-SI metric unit of mass equal to 1,000 kilograms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Tonne

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device that captures and records physical touch or embrace on a device and/or object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Touch Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ultrasonic sensors are used to deduce human posture in smart home for example.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ultrasonic Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The state of being able to see or be seen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Visibility

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect Visibility.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Visibility Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The SI unit of electromotive force, the difference of potential that would carry one ampere of current against one ohm resistance.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Volt

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: In electric power transmission and distribution, volt-ampere reactive (var) is a unit in which reactive power is expressed in an AC electric power system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Volt Ampere Reactive, VAR

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A device designed to respond to physical stimuli such as temperature, light, magnetism, or movement, and to transmit resulting impulses for interpretation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Voltage Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The height reached by the water in a reservoir, river, storage tank, or similar.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Water Level

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sea surface temperature (SST) is the water temperature close to the ocean's surface.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Water Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the SI unit of power, equivalent to one joule per second, corresponding to the rate of consumption of energy in an electric circuit where the potential difference is one volt and the current one ampere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Watt (W)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: It is the SI unit for radiative and other energy fluxes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Watt Per Square Metre, Watt Per Square Meter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Luminosity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Weather Luminosity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Weather Precipitation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Weather Precipitation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A body's relative mass or the quantity of matter contained by it, giving rise to a downward force; the heaviness of a person or thing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Weight

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to weight an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Weight Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The cooling effect of wind blowing on a surface.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind Chill

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect Wind Chill.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind Chill Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The geodetic azimuth of the direction from which the wind is blowing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind Direction

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device used to detect wind direction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind Direction Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The ratio of the distance covered by moving air to the time quantity taken to cover it.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind Velocity, Wind Speed

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Wind Speed Sensor, Anemometer or Wind Velocity Sensor is used to measure the wind speed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind Speed Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicator of whether a person (or object) is working or not
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Working State

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Year as a unit of time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Year

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The concentration of ozone (O3) gas suspended in the atmosphere.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Chemical Agent Atmospheric Concentration O3

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A unit of measure, or unit, is a particular quantity value that has been chosen as a scale for measuring other quantities the same kind (more generally of equivalent dimension). For example, the meter is a quantity of length that has been rigorously defined and standardized by the BIPM (International Board of Weights and Measures). Any measurement of the length can be expressed as a number multiplied by the unit meter. More formally, the value of a physical quantity Q with respect to a unit (U) is expressed as the scalar multiple of a real number (n) and U, as Q = nU.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An actuator to put the blinds up or down.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Blind Actuator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A sensor that measures heat capacity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Calorimeter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Designed to condition several spaces from one base location.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Central HVAC

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Dissolved oxygen refers to the level of free, non-compound oxygen present in water or other liquids. It is an important parameter in assessing water quality because of its influence on the organisms living within a body of water (Source: http://www.fondriest.com/environmental-measurements/parameters/water-quality/dissolved-oxygen).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dissolved Oxygen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A sensor that measures the amount of electric energy consumed by a residence, a business, or an electrically powered device (Source:Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Electricity Meter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment:
Represents a simplification of a real-world HVAC system.
Heating, Ventilation and Air Conditioning (HVAC) is the technology of indoor and vehicular environmental comfort (Wikipedia)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: HVAC

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents HVAC control strategies made by HVAC systems.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: HVAC Control Strategy

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of the Relative Humidity Indoors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Indoor Relative Humidity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of indoor temperature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Indoor Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An actuator to switch lights on and off.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Light Actuator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Designed to condition a single space (or portion of a space) from a location within or directly adjacent to the space.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Local HVAC

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The maximum speed of the wind.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Max Wind Speed

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ammonia or azane is a compound of nitrogen and hydrogen with the formula NH3 (Wikipedia)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: NH3

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Otophosphate level.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ortophosphate

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of the Relative Humidity Outdoors
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Outdoor Relative Humidity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Measure of outdoor temperature
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Outdoor Temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The power per unit area received from the Sun in the form of electromagnetic radiation in the wavelength range of the measuring instrument (Source: Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Solar Irradiance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ratio of time on which a space is occupied by people, animals or things within a given period of time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Space Occupancy

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Total suspended solids (TSS) is the dry-weight of particles trapped by a filter. It is a water quality parameter used for example to assess the quality of wastewater after treatment in a wastewater treatment plant (Source: Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Suspended Solids

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Conductivity of the water.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Water Conductivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The volume of water which passes per unit time (Source Wikipedia)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Water Flow

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Turbidity is the cloudiness or haziness of a fluid caused by large numbers of individual particles that are generally invisible to the naked eye, similar to smoke in air. The measurement of turbidity is a key test of water quality (Source: Wikipedia).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Water Turbidity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Wind's average cubic speed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind Power

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Sigma Speed of the wind
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind Sigma Theta

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The sigma of wind speed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind Speed Sigma

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An actuation is the execution of some actuating procedure by some actuator, and has an impact on the physical world.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actuation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An actuator is a device that implements some actuating procedure, and has thus an impact on the physical world.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Actuator
